[2026-04-03T19:20:07+05:30] [PHASE 3, TASK 4.1 - SRE RECOVERY] ZooKeeper readiness probe failure diagnosed and resolved.
[2026-04-03T19:20:07+05:30] [ANALYSIS] ROOT CAUSE: cp-zookeeper:7.5.0 ships ZooKeeper 3.5+ which disables all 4LW commands by default. readinessProbe (echo ruok | nc localhost 2181 | grep imok) returned empty string -> grep imok exited 1 -> ZooKeeper pod remained 0/1 NotReady -> Kafka session negotiation rejected -> Kafka CrashLoopBackOff -> wikipulse-worker CrashLoopBackOff.
[2026-04-03T19:20:07+05:30] [FIX APPLIED] k8s/infrastructure.yaml ZooKeeper Deployment patched: (1) Added KAFKA_OPTS=-Dzookeeper.4lw.commands.whitelist=ruok to re-enable ruok 4LW via JVM system property. (2) Updated readinessProbe to nc -w 1 (fail-fast 1s timeout). (3) Increased initialDelaySeconds 15->20 to cover JVM cold-start + leader election.
[2026-04-03T19:20:07+05:30] [BUILD GATE] .\mvnw clean compile -> BUILD SUCCESS. Exit code: 0. No Java source modifications required (pure Kubernetes infrastructure concern).

